          "label": "Scaling Colorspace",
          "param": "scaling_colorspace",
          "value_schema": {
            "default": "",
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        {
          "aliases": [
            "unsharp"
          ],
          "description": "Post-resize unsharp mask strength (0 = none, 100 = maximum).  Applied as a separate pass AFTER resampling. Adds real computational cost proportional to output dimensions. For zero-cost sharpening that adjusts the resampling kernel itself, use `kernel_lobe_ratio`.  None = no unsharp mask.",
          "key": "f.sharpen",
          "label": "Unsharp Mask",
          "param": "unsharp_percent",
          "value_schema": {
            "default": 0.0,
            "maximum": 100.0,
            "minimum": 0.0,
            "type": "number"
          }
        },
        {
          "aliases": [
            "kernel_lobe_ratio"
          ],
          "description": "Negative-lobe ratio for kernel sharpening (zero-cost).  Adjusts the resampling kernel's negative lobes during weight computation. 0.0 = flatten (maximum smoothness), above filter's natural ratio = sharpen. Zero additional cost — changes the filter shape, not a separate processing step.  For post-resize unsharp mask (separate pass), use `unsharp_percent`.",
          "key": "lobe_ratio",
          "label": "Lobe Ratio",
          "param": "kernel_lobe_ratio",
          "value_schema": {
            "default": 0.0,
            "maximum": 1.0,
            "minimum": 0.0,
            "type": "number"
          }
        },
        {
          "description": "When to apply resampling.  - \"size_differs\" — only resample when dimensions change (default) - \"size_differs_or_sharpening_requested\" — resample when dimensions change or when sharpening is requested (allows sharpening without resize) - \"always\" — always resample, even at identity dimensions",
          "key": "resample_when",
          "label": "Resample When",
          "param": "resample_when",
          "value_schema": {
            "default": "size_differs",
            "type": "string"
